name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: If you’re donating money through crowdfunding, thank you for your generosity. This publication has tips on protecting yourself and the $ you’re donating. For any questions, the Charities Division of my office is here to help.  https://t.co/fj2XgWNv0j

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: There are broader lessons here for everyone. If you’re raising $ thru crowdfunding for a charitable (not personal) purpose, there are laws you need to comply with even if you’re not a nonprofit or 501c3. Read this to know your legal responsibilities.  https://t.co/Srqcm8t8Yk

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Philando Castile cared deeply about the children he served & the children loved him back. Not using every dollar raised in his name to help children was an insult to his legacy & his loved ones. I’ve made sure all the $ raised will now help those kids.  https://t.co/TGLxdfAJC6

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: There are real people and stories behind the 5,550 MNs lost to the opioid crisis. The money should go where the pain is.  Passing HF 4265 will provide relief by getting $300 million to Minnesota communities for treatment, abatement, and prevention where it’s needed most. #mnleg  https://t.co/hfew9RK9GX

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: No amount of money can ever make up for the death & destruction that opioid companies caused in MN but we’ve still held them accountable.   Passing HF 4265 brings relief by getting $300 million to MN communities for treatment, abatement & prevention where it’s needed most. #mnleg  https://t.co/USoSJnD5ux

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: I’ve stood up for kids before: I asked FB to ditch plans for Insta for kids & joined national investigations of Insta & TikTok for promoting their platforms despite known harms. It’s all our job to help the youngest & most vulnerable Minnesotans live w dignity, safety & respect.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: The harms of social media use on children are real, up to & incl bullying & self-harm. I joined a bipartisan group of 44 AGs asking TikTok & Snapchat to do more to let parents protect their kids. I’ll keep using my office to make sure our kids are safe.  https://t.co/s0xRAZ6AKM

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: More detail about the settlement & link to original lawsuit here. Thanks very much to Philando’s mother Valerie Castile for all her support along the way and for being a powerful moral leader.  https://t.co/aAakSXjW1S

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Farmers, ranchers, and all Ag workers are the backbone of Minnesota: they sustain their families and communities and put food on all our tables. name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: In 2019 & 20 I led state AGs asking the Trump admin to cancel student debt for DreamCenter students. They did a very limited amount but should have done much more. I renewed the call last December with the Biden admin. I’m optimistic they're moving closer. I'll keep fighting.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Just a few wks ago I led a coalition of AGs in getting the current holders of DreamCenter’s private student debt to cancel it. That put $2.1M back into the pockets of students who were left with debt & nothing to show for it through no fault of their own.  https://t.co/jY8gETnqyG

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Too many students have been left out to dry when mismanaged for-profit schools suddenly close. I’ve been fighting for years for debt relief for students of DreamCenter schools & will keep fighting until they get the relief they deserve.  https://t.co/ko4ktM0wWj

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: MN is a state with a proud Ag heritage and corporate greed is pushing family farmers out.  This is simply wrong. We’re not going to stand by and let the family farmer continue to struggle.  We're committed to protecting family farmers and fighting marking consolidation.  https://t.co/PJ30ylJemN

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Let me tell Minnesotans something disturbing: We're one of 13 states that don't have a statute against price-gouging.   We're at the legislature urging them to pass an anti-price gouging law on behalf of MN consumers.  https://t.co/bqvDcbe7XD

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Fighting corporate greed is one of the most important issues of our time.   It's key to a fair economy, opportunity, and the American Dream.  By beefing up MN’s antitrust laws, we can protect MNs from the harms of market concentration.  I’m supporting HF 4142, 4143 & 4144.  https://t.co/tj61ZGy5Av

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Anticompetitive behavior—esp in ag, tech & healthcare—hurts purchasing power, innovation & wages. We need to beef up MN’s antitrust laws to better fight corporate greed & protect Minnesotans everywhere from the harms of market concentration.  I’m supporting HF 4142, 4143 & 4144.  https://t.co/i8cWowyXDo

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: It’s tough to afford our lives these days & no increase in utility bills is welcome. In the face of the utilities’ armies of lawyers & lobbyists, the small but tough team in my office fights only for your interests. As long as I’m AG we’ll keep doing that.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: As a result, the PUC gave CenterPoint a 3.9% increase instead for the 6.6% they asked for. We also fought to make sure residential customers as a class pay a smaller share of the increase that CenterPoint wanted. We won that too.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: We fought to keep your basic monthly charge flat. We fought to keep company expenses like marketing prog that would entrench consumer reliance on natural gas, annual dues for organizations that cater to shareholders & excessive company expenses off your bill. We won those fights.

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Part of my job as AG is to fight for residential customers at the PUC when utilities ask for more $. It’s tough to afford your life these days so when CenterPoint asked for more, we fought to bring down their increase & succeeded in knocking $18M off it.  https://t.co/WaaZNa0HwJ

name: Attorney General Keith Ellison
tweet: Today is #EqualPayday2022. Women deserve equal pay for equal work. Full stop.   My task force on Expanding the Economic Security of Women has over 100 recommendations on removing barriers so women can fully participate in our economy.   Read our report:  https://t.co/3yew5k1W88  https://t.co/YZ0v9Pl7ar
